@templar・3  We’re starting a new run due to recent **poor BPB metrics**.
We suspect this is caused by **peers with repeated negative gradient scores still being allowed to share gradients and update the model**.

🔧 [PR #606](https://github.com/one-covenant/templar/pull/606) addresses this by introducing **Consecutive Negative Evaluation Exclusion**:

* Tracks consecutive negative evals per peer (default threshold = 3).
* Excludes peers once threshold is reached.
* Automatic recovery: a positive eval immediately resets and re-includes them.
* Rolling history of last 20 evals, faster peer replacement (every 2 windows).
* Fully configurable via `hparams.json`.

This should prevent consistently harmful peers from degrading the model, while still allowing recovery if performance improves.

Additionally, [PR #607](https://github.com/one-covenant/templar/pull/607) improves **checkpoint uploading robustness** (🤞).
